SIMPLE: inimical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inimical
<hw>In*im"i*cal</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inimicalis</ets>, fr. <ets>inimicus</ets> unfriendly, hostile;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>amicus</ets> friendly. See
<er>Amity</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the disposition or temper of an enemy;
unfriendly; unfavorable; -- chiefly applied to <xex>private</xex>, as
<xex>hostile</xex> is to <xex>public</xex>, enmity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Opposed in tendency, influence, or effects;
antagonistic; inconsistent; incompatible; adverse; repugnant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We are at war with a system, which, by its essence, is
<qex>inimical</qex> to all other governments.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inimicality</ent>⟦br⟧
